Reason
------
Routines is a six-part plan (`docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-13-routines-design.md`)
whose parts land on main independently:

  1/6  core engine crate (tuxlink-routines)            — landed
  2/6  actions + arbiter + Tauri mount (tuxlink-ofw4s) — in progress
  3/6  validator + dry-run (tuxlink-pgidw)             — landed
  4/6  MCP tools + one-cadence amendment (tuxlink-oiigb) — in progress
  5/6  (not yet filed)
  6/6  (not yet filed)

v0.91.0 already shipped with parts of this on main. Every further nightly would cut
another release carrying a partially-built feature — the exact failure this marker was
created for (release-please.yml: "v0.55.0 shipped the Phase-3 transmit gate ahead of its
enabling Phase 6"). Hold releases until Routines lands as a coherent whole.

Why Routines specifically, and not just "wait for tidiness"
-----------------------------------------------------------
Routines SCHEDULES RF ACTIONS. Its v1 scope includes the scheduler, the radio arbiter,
the three-layer validator, and the Part 97 consent-closure layer. A release that carries
the scheduling half without its guards is not merely incoherent — it is the wrong half to
ship first. The consent-closure validator exists precisely so a routine cannot be
authored that would transmit outside an operator's control; shipping a routine engine
ahead of a complete guard is the failure mode RADIO-1 and ADR 0022 both exist to prevent.

Routines is currently INERT in the shipped binary — the crate is present but has no Tauri
mount and no frontend surface (`grep -c routines src-tauri/src/lib.rs` = 0 as of
de0a3126). That is what makes freezing NOW cheap: part 2/6 is "actions + arbiter + Tauri
mount", and the moment it lands the feature becomes partially REACHABLE. Freeze before
the mount, not after.

What this does and does not stop
--------------------------------
- STOPS: release-please opening/updating the rolling release PR (release-please.yml),
  and the nightly release-merge cron merging + tagging it (release-merge.yml).
- DOES NOT STOP: feature-branch PRs merging to main as normal. Work continues; it just
  does not accumulate into an auto-tagged release.

Unfreeze
--------
Delete this file in a PR once Routines is complete and wire-walked end to end — all six
parts landed, the operator-facing surface reachable, and the operator approves a release
cut. Per ADR 0022 completeness is an invariant: "most of Routines" is not a reason to
unfreeze.

